The paper deals with learning a representation of haptic feedback for manipulation tasks on a robot, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of deep recurrent neural networks and variational Bayes methods suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The tasks involve physical interaction with objects, which could involve computer vision (cs.CV) for object recognition. Finally, the use of a partially observable Markov decision process (POMDP) suggests a focus on control systems (cs.SY).
